// Brute Force
// Time: O(nÂ²)
// Space: O(26) ~ O(1)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
/**
 * Problem: 3713. Longest Balanced Substring I
 *
 * ğŸ’¡ Intuition (Soch kya hai?)
 * Humein string ka sabse lamba substring find karna hai jisme:
 * ğŸ‘‰ Jo bhi characters present ho us substring mein,
 * ğŸ‘‰ Un sabki frequency exactly same ho.
 *
 * Example:
 * "aabb" âœ” (a=2, b=2 â†’ balanced)
 * "aabbb" âŒ (a=2, b=3 â†’ not balanced)
 *
 * --------------------------------------------------------
 *
 * ğŸ§  Approach (Brute Force - All Substrings Check karna)
 *
 * 1. Har possible starting index 'i' se substring banana start karte hain.
 * 2. Ek frequency array (size 26) maintain karte hain jo har character ka count store karega.
 * 3. Har ending index 'j' tak substring extend karte hain.
 * 4. Har step par check karte hain ki:
 *      - Jo bhi characters aaye hain unki frequency equal hai ya nahi.
 * 5. Agar balanced hai â†’ max length update kar dete hain.
 *
 * --------------------------------------------------------
 *
 * âš™ï¸ Kaise check ho raha hai balanced?
 *
 * checkBalancedFreq():
 * - Pehle non-zero frequency ko reference bana lete hain.
 * - Fir baaki sab non-zero frequencies compare karte hain.
 * - Agar sab same hai â†’ substring balanced.
 * - Agar ek bhi alag mila â†’ false.
 *
 * --------------------------------------------------------
 */
class Solution {
    public int longestBalanced(String s) {
        int n = s.length();

        int maxLen = 0;

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        {
            int[] freq = new int[26];

            for(int j = i; j < n; j++)
            {
                char ch = s.charAt(j);
                freq[ch - 97]++;

                if(checkBalancedFreq(freq))
                    maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, j - i + 1);
            }
        }

        return maxLen;
    }

    public boolean checkBalancedFreq(int[] freq)
    {
        int count = 0;

        for(int i = 0; i < 26; i++)
        {
            if(freq[i] == 0)
                continue;
            
            if(count == 0)
                count = freq[i];
            else if(freq[i] != count)
                return false;
        }

        return true;
    }
}
